style.single_player_with_npc_prompt:
### Instruction:
{name}'s persona: {bio}
Write a fictional never-ending spoken conversation in {language} between {name} and {player_name} at {time12} {time_group} in {location} in Skyrim. Separate messages with double newlines.
Context:
{context}
The following are Behaviors that {name} can use in addition to responding to {perspective_player_name}.
If {perspective_player_name} wants {name} to do something and {name} of them want to do it, {name} MUST use the appropriate Action Keyword before their next response. Actions will be used even if they're not the exact phrasing used in the example.
Available Actions:
{behavior_summary}
Available Keywords: {behavior_keywords}
Develop the conversation slowly, and always stay in character, using spoken dialog and *visible actions in asterisks (and not using 'internal monologue narration' style - this is a movie, not a book) as provided by the character's persona.
The following is a summary of the spoken conversation that {name} and {perspective_player_name} have had so far:
{memories}
### Conversation:
{name}:

style.single_npc_with_npc_prompt:
### Instruction:
{name1} is a {race1} {gendered_age1} that lives in Skyrim. {name1} can only speak {language}. {name1}'s persona: {bio1}
{name2} is a {race2} {gendered_age2} that lives in Skyrim. {name2} can only speak {language2}. {name2}'s persona: {bio2}
Write a fictional never-ending spoken conversation in {language} between {name1} and {name2} at {time12} {time_group} in {location} in Skyrim. Separate messages with double newlines.
Context:
{context}
Develop the conversation slowly, and always stay in character, using spoken dialog and occasional *visible action descriptions* wrapped in single asterisks (and not using 'internal monologue narration' style - this is a movie, not a book) as provided by the character's persona. Treat *text in asterisks* as visible events. Treat [text in brackets] as instruction. System is not really there, no one will hear what System said, but they will know it. System is the narrator explaining the state of the world.
The following is a summary of the spoken conversations that {name1} and {name2} have had so far:
{conversation_summary1}
{conversation_summary2}
### Conversation:
{name1}:
